        "title": "fix(ci): bundle test shards and right-size runners",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- bundle only low-risk infra, cron, and command Node include-pattern shards into deterministic jobs capped at 64 test files, reducing the normal Node matrix from 95 planned shards to 63\n- keep agents-core and gateway/server suites isolated after live validation showed shared mock state makes arbitrary bundling unsafe\n- route lower-weight bundles and fixed lanes to 4 vCPU while retaining measured heavy suites on 8 vCPU\n- right-size `build-artifacts` from 32 to 16 vCPU and Windows checks from 16 to 8 vCPU\n- keep PR/main supersession cancellation enabled and document the runner allocation contract\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.tooling.config.ts --reporter=dot test/scripts/ci-node-test-plan.test.ts test/scripts/ci-workflow-guards.test.ts`\n- result: 2 files, 41 tests passed\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run -- env OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 corepack pnpm check:changed`\n- Crabbox run: `run_68218ee27622` (exit 0)\n- autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- live CI run `27928007900`: 63 `checks-node-*` jobs materialized; no bundled gateway/agents-core failures. Remaining failures match current `main` baseline suites (`build-artifacts`, lint, extension bundle, agents-core/runtime/models, embedded, plugin SDK, core fast/tooling).\n",
